article.headline: David Lipscomb 69, Hawaii 63
article.story:
HONOLULU (AP) -- Courtney Boynton had 15 points as Lipscomb edged
Hawaii 69-63 Saturday in the semifinals of the Waikiki Beach
Marriott Classic.

It was the Rainbow Wahine's first season-opening loss after 14
consecutive opening victories.

Lipscomb (1-0) will face Washington, an 82-70 victor over Maine,
on Sunday evening in the championship game.

Hawaii sank one more basket than Lipscomb (23-22), but the Lady
Bisons were more accurate from long range. They hit 10 of their 22
3-point attempts, while the Rainbow Wahine made just four of their
22 tries.

Kendra Ramsey and Angie Ester added 10 points apiece for
Lipscomb.

April Atuaia had 17 points for Hawaii. Teammates Milia
Macfarlane and Amy Sanders had nine points each.
